text: Bourgogne-Fresne is a commune. It is in Grand Est in the Marne department in northeast France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2017 and consists of the former communes of Bourgogne (the seat) and Fresne-lès-Reims.Arrêté préfectoral 27 June 2016 == Related pages == * Communes of the Marne department == References == Category:2017 establishments in France Category:Communes in Marne
title: Bourgogne-Fresne
